{
  "texts": [
    "This type of error, where an early mistake can lead to the failure of an entire sequence of tasks, underscores the critical need for dynamic task decomposition.",
    "Regarding other types of errors, our analysis indicates that the TDAG method generally exhibits low error rates across CKE, EIM and CNC errors.",
    "This improvement is attributed to the ability of dynamically generated subagents to focus on specific subtasks, leveraging their tailored capabilities to navigate the intricacies of each challenge effectively.",
    "Notably, ReAct outperforms more complex approaches in minimizing EIM errors.",
    "A possible reason could be that complex methods generate excessive context, which may increase the likelihood of hallucination phenomena."
  ]
}